The article reports that President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued an Executive Order imposing sanctions on Russia due to its ongoing war against Ukraine, including its recent invasion in violation of international law. The Executive Order prohibits the importation of various products of Russian origin into the United States, such as crude oil, petroleum, liquefied natural gas, coal, and coal products. It also prohibits new investment in the energy sector in Russia by US individuals or entities, as well as any approval, financing, facilitation, or guarantee of transactions by US individuals or entities that would be prohibited under this order. The President states that Russia's actions pose an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security and foreign policy of the United States. The Executive Order was issued on March 8, 2022.